  "market_context": "ETH was in a range with equal lows swept to the left and a high above. Price purged the range low and closed back inside, suggesting accumulation followed by potential distribution higher. Daily candles began closing over the previous day's equilibrium.",
  "key_observation": "Each successive daily candle respected the upper half (0.5 EQ) of the previous day's range to trade higher, forming higher-time-frame wicks and confirming bullish expansion through PD array matching in the upper half.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the range context: equal lows swept to the left, high above, with price purging the range low and closing back inside — signalling potential bullish distribution.",
    "Noted that price closed over the previous day's equilibrium, signalling the upper half should be respected.",
    "Dropped to the 1H timeframe and mapped PD arrays in the upper half of the prior day's range: a small fair value gap and a protected low formed from a FVG rebalance.",
    "Anticipated the New York session for expansion; observed price consolidate, ignore an unrespected FVG, then reach into the opposing candles.",
    "Confirmed change in state of delivery when price closed through the down-close candles, sweeping lows.",
    "Watched price respect the upper-half PD array, form a continuation candle, and expand higher into the next day.",
    "Repeated the same process the following day: closed over previous day's high, marked EQ, identified small FVG and protected low in the upper half, anticipated continuation higher.",
    "Observed price reach into opposing candles, close over them forming the higher-time-frame wick, and continue toward failure swings on the other side of the range."
  ],
  "outcome": "Bullish continuation played out — each day respected the previous day's equilibrium, expanded higher, and eventually took out the failure swings on the other side of the range.",
  "lessons": "In expansion phases, anticipate the upper half (above EQ) of the previous candle's range to support price higher in bullish scenarios. Match PD arrays inside that upper half and use protected lows as invalidation rather than expecting deep retracements into discount.",
